headline: US Stock Market Today: S&P 500 Futures Climb amid Higher-for-Longer Rate Jitters
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Monday, Dec, 15 2025 US stock futures are pointing higher this morning, with the E mini S&P 500 up about 0.4 percent, as investors weigh rising borrowing costs against a packed week of economic scorecards. The 10 year Treasury yield is nearing 4.2 percent after Federal Reserve officials hinted at fewer interest rate cuts next year, which simply means mortgages, credit cards and business loans may stay expensive for longer.
